17 Such teams shall be composed of a licensed psychiatrist, and representatives from the
18 hospital or psychiatric residential treatment facility, Division of Family and Children
19 Services of the Department of Human Services; the Department of Juvenile Justice; the
20 Department of Early Care and Learning; the Department of Public Health; the
21 Department of Community Health; the Department of Insurance; the Department of
22 Education; the Office of the Child Advocate for the Protection of Children; and the
23 Department of Corrections. Additionally, such term may include the referring physician.
24 (b) Every hospital and psychiatric residential treatment facility in this state shall adhere
25 to the following procedures for instances in which the parent, guardian, or legal custodian
26 of a child who has received psychiatric care or acute psychiatric care at such hospital or
27 facility fails to take physical custody of such child within 48 hours of a physician's
28 discharge order from such hospital or facility:
29 (1) Assemble a MATCH team to determine the best placement for the child; and
30 (2) Without delay, place such child into an appropriate environment which may include,
31 but is not limited to, the child's family home, a foster home, a kinship home, a community
32 based or medical facility, or such other environment as the MATCH team may determine
33 appropriate. If necessary to ensure that such placement occurs without delay, the
34 MATCH team shall meet on an emergency basis."
35 SECTION 2.
36 Each MATCH team affected by this Act shall submit such information as may be requested
37 by the Department of Human Services. Such department shall submit a report to the
38 chairpersons of the House Appropriations Committee and the Senate Appropriations
39 Committee by December 31 of the year following the year in which this Act becomes
40 effective. Such report shall include the number of children and length of stay of such
41 children at a hospital or psychiatric residential treatment facility during the year that the
42 report is submitted but for a period time no later than December 1 of that year.
